quote: The end is in the beginning and yet you go on.
author: Samuel Beckett,  Endgame

quote: Ends are not bad things, they just mean that something else is about to begin. And there are many things that don't really end, anyway, they just begin again in a new way. Ends are not bad and many ends aren't really an ending; some things are never-ending.
author: C. JoyBell C.

quote: End with an image and don't explain.
author: Stanley Kunitz,  The Collected Poems

quote: This is not the end, this is not even the beginning of the end, this is just perhaps the end of the beginning.
author: Winston S. Churchill

quote: But whateverHoweverWhenever this ends I want you to knowThat right nowI love you forever
author: Andrea Gibson,  How It Ends

quote: Ends are for yesterday, not tomorrows.
author: Mitch Albom,  The Time Keeper

quote: This is your life and its ending one moment at a time.
author: Chuck Palahniuk,  Fight Club

quote: There are no happy endings.Endings are the saddest part, So just give me a happy middleAnd a very happy start.
author: Shel Silverstein,  Every Thing on It

quote: Death, a necessary end, will come when it will come
author: William Shakespeare,  Julius Caesar

quote: Life begins where needs end.
author: Debasish Mridha

quote: End? No, the journey doesn't end here. Death is just another path. One that we all must take.
author: J.R.R. Tolkien,  The Return of the King

quote: This is the way the world endsNot with a bang but a whimper.
author: T.S. Eliot

quote: There is no real ending. It’s just the place where you stop the story.
author: Frank Herbert

quote: Your love story, I don’t want to give away the ending, but both you and your lover die.
author: Jarod Kintz,  Love quotes for the ages. Specifically ages 18-81.

quote: Life's like a movie, write your own ending. Keep believing, keep pretending.
author: Jim Henson

quote: Success is Never Ending, Failure Is Never Final.
author: Robert A. Schuller

quote: If you own this story you get to write the ending.
author: Brené Brown

quote: I want my world to start and end with you.
author: E.L. James,  Fifty Shades of Grey

quote: This is your life, and its ending one minute at a time.
author: Chuck Palahniuk,  Fight Club

quote: I let myself have feelings for you despite not knowing how this would end.
author: Siobhan Vivian,  Not That Kind of Girl

quote: Death isn't the end, it's the beginning.
author: Jennifer Love Hewitt

quote: Every beginning has an end and every end is a new beginning.
author: Santosh Kalwar,  Quote Me Everyday

quote: You here to finish me off, Sweetheart?
author: Suzanne Collins,  The Hunger Games

quote: The end may justify the means as long as there is something that justifies the end.
author: Leon Trotsky,  Their Morals and Ours

quote: Let everything happen to youBeauty and terrorJust keep goingNo feeling is final
author: Rainer Maria Rilke

quote: I'm ending this.''No. Come on. It's not worth it.''You are,' he said fiercely, looking at her.'You're worth it.
author: Rainbow Rowell,  Eleanor & Park

quote: End? No, the journey doesn't end here. Death is just another path, one that we all must take. The grey rain-curtain of this world rolls back, and all turns to silver glass, and then you see it.
author: J.R.R. Tolkien

quote: Everything ends in death, everything. Death is terrible.
author: Leo Tolstoy,  War and Peace

quote: In the end, the end of a life only matters to friends, family, and other folks you used to know. For everyone else, it's just another end.
author: Gabrielle Zevin

quote: I will follow you to the ends of the world.
author: Khaled Hosseini,  A Thousand Splendid Suns

quote: My happiness is not the means to any end. It is the end. It is its own goal. It is its own purpose.
author: Ayn Rand,  Anthem

quote: Life's not black-and-white. Sometimes the ends justifies the means.
author: Emily Giffin,  Something Borrowed

quote: It is good to have an end to journey toward; but it is the journey that matters, in the end.
author: Ernest Hemingway

quote: Every beginning has an end and every end has a new beginning, don't worry, broken soul, life will one day come to an end.
author: Santosh Kalwar

quote: There are no happy endings... There are no endings, happy or otherwise. We all have our own stories which are just part of the one Story that binds both this world and Faerie. Sometimes we step into each others stories - perhaps just for a few minutes, perhaps for years - and then we step out of them again. But all the while, the Story just goes on.
author: Charles de Lint,  Dreams Underfoot

quote: Reading is not an end to itself, but a means to an end.
author: Adolf Hitler,  Mein Kampf

quote: But as long as something is never even started, you never have to worry about it ending. It has endless potential.
author: Sarah Dessen,  The Truth About Forever

quote: The day is ending. It's time for something that was beautiful to turn into something else that is beautiful. Now, Let go.
author: Elizabeth Gilbert,  Eat, Pray, Love

quote: A good book has no ending.
author: R. D. Cumming

quote: In the end, the world always wins. That's just the way of things.
author: Khaled Hosseini,  The Kite Runner

quote: Now begin in the middle, and later learn the beginning; the end will take care of itself.
author: Harlan Ellison

quote: I think the end goal, hopefully, is to take advantage of the attention I've gotten along the way and use it for good and build some communities, and as I get older I can continue to do things and be surrounded by things that are inspirational to me.
author: Reggie Watts

quote: At the end to death I must go,Finishing a real tragic and funny show.
author: Mohit K. Misra

quote: These violent delights have violent ends.
author: William Shakespeare,  Romeo and Juliet

quote: God wants us to know that life is a series of beginnings, not endings. Just as graduations are not terminations, but commencements. Creation is an ongoing process, and when we create a perfect world where love and compassion are shared by all, suffering will cease.
author: Bernie Siegel

quote: And don't tell me the end justifies the means because it doesn't. We never reach the end. All we ever get is means. That's what we live with.
author: Nick Harkaway,  Angelmaker

quote: What’s the opposite of start? Would the average person think stop or finish? The answer may reflect the difference between a winner and a loser.
author: Jarod Kintz,  The Days of Yay are Here! Wake Me Up When They're Over.

quote: And where love ends, hate begins
author: Leo Tolstoy,  Anna Karenina

quote: Endings are not always bad. Most times they're just beginnings in disguise.
author: Kim Harrison,  Something Deadly This Way Comes

quote: You’ve gone far away to a place with no horses and very little grass, and you’re studying how to write a story with a happy ending. If you can write that ending for yourself, maybe you can come back.
author: Jennifer Echols,  Love Story
